    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as a single-page, scrollable dashboard, abandoning the linear report structure for a more intuitive, story-driven flow. It starts with a Hero section stating the vision, then moves to an interactive "Core Flywheel" (the 3 components). This leads to the "Value Engine" (how value is created), followed by the "Strategic Levers" (what enables the engine). Next is "The Blueprint," combining architecture and monetization interactively. A "Lessons from Giants" section provides comparative analysis of other platforms using an interactive chart. It concludes with an interactive "Roadmap." This thematic, top-down structure is designed to guide the user from the high-level vision to the detailed implementation, making complex relationships easier to understand and explore. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Core Components: Goal: Organize/Relate. Method: Interactive HTML/CSS diagram instead of a static list. Interaction: Hovering over each component reveals its description. Justification: Visually shows the interconnectedness central to the report's thesis. Library: Tailwind CSS.
        - Value Mechanisms: Goal: Explain/Organize. Method: Interactive cards. Interaction: Clicking a card reveals detailed text. Justification: Breaks down the four complex mechanisms into digestible, user-initiated chunks. Library: Vanilla JS, Tailwind.
        - Strategic Levers: Goal: Inform/Relate. Method: Interactive HTML/CSS diagram of levers. Interaction: Clicking a lever highlights it and displays its function. Justification: Creates a tangible metaphor for these key points. Library: Vanilla JS, Tailwind.
        - Platform Comparison: Goal: Compare. Method: Interactive grouped bar chart. Interaction: Users can see relative strengths across platforms. Justification: Transforms the dense Table 4 into a clear, insightful visual comparison. Library: Chart.js.
        - Monetization Models: Goal: Compare. Method: Radar chart. Interaction: Visually compares the monetization mix of Cuvisoft vs. industry leaders. Justification: Effectively shows the strategic positioning and diversity of Cuvisoft's proposed revenue streams. Library: Chart.js.
        - Implementation Roadmap: Goal: Show Change/Process. Method: Interactive horizontal timeline. Interaction: Clicking a phase displays detailed plans. Justification: More engaging and space-efficient than a long text list. Library: Vanilla JS, Tailwind.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
